<head>KNEE</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">膝</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">膝</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BIG JOINT in the MIDDLE of the LEG.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current word for the knee as a whole is xī 膝.</p>
<p>2. Bìn 臏 is the technical term for a knee-cap which is not so infrequently mentioned because it was sometimes removed by way of punishment.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
